                            <comment id="409486" author="JIRAUSER18707" created="Fri, 29 Mar 2024 18:26:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Peter,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Got it. Thank you so much.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Jane&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="409469" author="pjones" created="Fri, 29 Mar 2024 15:45:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jane&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No you cannot. You could build 2.15.4 against el8.7 if you wished to stay on a specific kernel version but older Lustre versions will not build against more current Linux distributions (unless you backport the patches that added in this support- again, not something we would encourage/support - we produce the maintenance releases to make this unnecessary)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="409426" author="JIRAUSER18707" created="Fri, 29 Mar 2024 04:07:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Peter,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for response. In this case, I want to keep the same Lustre version, 2.15.2, across all OSS servers. My additional question is, can we install the Lustre 2.15.2 RPMs meant for el8.7 (found at &lt;a href=&quot;https://downloads.whamcloud.com/public/lustre/lustre-2.15.2/el8.7/server/RPMS/x86_64/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://downloads.whamcloud.com/public/lustre/lustre-2.15.2/el8.7/server/RPMS/x86_64/&lt;/a&gt;) on RHEL8.9? I can&apos;t find Lustre 2.15.2 RPMs for el8.9, and our servers are a mix of RHEL8.7 and RHEL8.9.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Jane&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="409400" author="pjones" created="Thu, 28 Mar 2024 21:13:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jane&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mixing versions among OSSes is only expecting to be a very short-lived state of affairs while upgrading and is only tested as such, so I cannot really say what the outcome would be. Given that the difference between the versions is small, it might well work without problems, but it would certainly not be a recommended or supported configuration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
